abstract: Former New York Mayor Michael Bloomberg was not on the ballot in Saturday's Democratic presidential primary in South Carolina, but he was still on voters' minds - and not in a good way.
snippet: Former New York Mayor Michael Bloomberg was not on the ballot in Saturday's Democratic presidential primary in South Carolina, but he was still on voters' minds - and not in a good way.
lead_paragraph: (Reuters) - Former New York Mayor Michael Bloomberg was not on the ballot in Saturday's Democratic presidential primary in South Carolina, but he was still on voters' minds - and not in a good way.
headline_main: Bloomberg in South Carolina: Not on the Ballot and Not Liked-Poll
headline_print_headline: Bloomberg in South Carolina: Not on the Ballot and Not Liked-Poll

abstract: Vice President Joe Biden has for weeks looked to the black voters of South Carolina to hand a win to his flagging campaign. On Saturday, they delivered.
snippet: Vice President Joe Biden has for weeks looked to the black voters of South Carolina to hand a win to his flagging campaign. On Saturday, they delivered.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Vice President Joe Biden has for weeks looked to the black voters of South Carolina to hand a win to his flagging campaign. On Saturday, they delivered.
headline_main: AP VoteCast: Black Voters Carry Biden to His First Victory
headline_print_headline: AP VoteCast: Black Voters Carry Biden to His First Victory

abstract: Voters in Saturday’s Democratic presidential primary election in South Carolina called health care the top issue facing the country today, clearly naming it as more important than the economy, climate change, immigration, race relations and guns.
snippet: Voters in Saturday’s Democratic presidential primary election in South Carolina called health care the top issue facing the country today, clearly naming it as more important than the economy, climate change, immigration, race relations and guns.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Voters in Saturday’s Democratic presidential primary election in South Carolina called health care the top issue facing the country today, clearly naming it as more important than the economy, climate change, immigration, race relations and guns.
headline_main: AP VoteCast: Voters Prioritize Health Care in South Carolina
headline_print_headline: AP VoteCast: Voters Prioritize Health Care in South Carolina

abstract: Socialist hardliners in Venezuela opened fire during a march headed by Juan Guaidó, injuring a 16-year-old demonstrator and adding to tensions in the country as the opposition leader seeks to revive his campaign to oust Nicolás Maduro.
snippet: Socialist hardliners in Venezuela opened fire during a march headed by Juan Guaidó, injuring a 16-year-old demonstrator and adding to tensions in the country as the opposition leader seeks to revive his campaign to oust Nicolás Maduro.
lead_paragraph: CARACAS, Venezuela — Socialist hardliners in Venezuela opened fire during a march headed by Juan Guaidó, injuring a 16-year-old demonstrator and adding to tensions in the country as the opposition leader seeks to revive his campaign to oust Nicolás Maduro.
headline_main: Socialist Hardliner Aims Gun on Guaidó March in Venezuela
headline_print_headline: Socialist Hardliner Aims Gun on Guaidó March in Venezuela

abstract: The Trump administration’s deal with the Taliban recognizes the limits of American power.
snippet: The Trump administration’s deal with the Taliban recognizes the limits of American power.
lead_paragraph: The deal the Trump administration signed with the Taliban on Saturday is a ticket out of Afghanistan for American troops who’ve been there far too long. It is a quiet end to a conflict that began with vibrant clarity, if not strategic vision, and descended into bloody ambiguity.

abstract: Seeking to draw a direct contrast with President Trump, Mr. Bloomberg will deliver a three-minute prerecorded address on the coronavirus outbreak in an ad on network television Sunday night.
snippet: Seeking to draw a direct contrast with President Trump, Mr. Bloomberg will deliver a three-minute prerecorded address on the coronavirus outbreak in an ad on network television Sunday night.
lead_paragraph: Seeking to draw a direct contrast with President Trump and present himself as the best Democratic alternative, Michael R. Bloomberg will deliver a three-minute prerecorded address on the coronavirus outbreak in an ad on network television Sunday night, his campaign announced.

headline_main: Michael Bloomberg Will Address Coronavirus in Prime-Time TV Ad

abstract: Several of the nation’s top health officials are among those sitting on an advisory panel formed by President Trump.
snippet: Several of the nation’s top health officials are among those sitting on an advisory panel formed by President Trump.
lead_paragraph: President Trump formed a coronavirus task force in late January, and members have been meeting regularly. But as the virus began to spread around the globe and infections were confirmed in the United States, Mr. Trump named Vice President Mike Pence as his point person at the end of February, and more administration officials were added to the panel. Among them are internationally known AIDS experts; a former drug executive; infectious disease doctors; and the former attorney general of Virginia.

headline_main: Who’s on the U.S. Coronavirus Task Force

abstract: Now, after many fire drills, the world may be facing a real fire.
snippet: Now, after many fire drills, the world may be facing a real fire.
lead_paragraph: Back in 2002, when the SARS virus made its fateful leap from bats to civet cats to humans, global health experts warned that the ensuing outbreak was a harbinger of things to come: Climate change and globalization were conspiring with an array of other forces to make it much easier for old animal diseases to morph into new human ones. It was only a matter of time before one of those diseases proved truly catastrophic. The world could avert the worst consequences if it started planning.
